    <p>Remi,</p>
    <p><br>
    </p>
    <p>Keep in mind this is still suboptimal.</p>
    <p>if you run 2 tasks per node, there is a risks threads from
      different ranks end up bound to the same core, which means time
      sharing and a drop in performance.</p>
    <p><br>
    </p>
    <p>Cheers,</p>
    <p><br>
    </p>
    <p>Gilles<br>
    </p>
    <br>
